räge des Bandes die Frage nach dem Eigensinn des Ethischen.  aWhat do we mean when we speak of ethical requirements or judgments? What is the task of philosophical ethics in public debates? How can the moral point of view orient us regarding competing economic, political, and legal demands? Today, philosophical ethics is under great pressure to become more scientific, and mostly specializes in working out specific follow-up costs of the mechanization of human life. But there is less and less clarity on how it should define itself and its task in the first place. Against this background, the contributions to this volume ask about the intrinsic purpose of the ethical.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 4aGesellschaftstheorie. 4aMetaethik. 4aMoral. 4aNormativität. 4aPhilosophie. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Ethics & Moral Philosophy.2bisacsh  aMetaethics.  aNormativity.  aPhilosophy.  aSocial Theory.1 aGamm, Gerhard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGamm, Gerhard, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGehring, Petra, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGerhardt, Volker, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHendrich, Geert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHetzel, Andreas, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHubig, Christoph, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLiebsch, Burkhard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMersch, Dieter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNordmann, Alfred, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRehbock, Theda, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchiller, Hans